node.text: There is no greater gift than time with family, friends, and loved ones. Wishing you and yours a Merry Christmas.

Happy Hanukkah! Sending my warmest wishes to those celebrating in the United States and around the world. May these eight nights be a time of reflection and hope as you gather with friends, family, or the family you create.

@gretathunberg has proven that one voice can make a difference. Her leadership in the international fight for climate justice has inspired countless young people to take up the charge for a more sustainable future. I hope our current leadership is listening.

⁣

Thank you @rashadny for having me on the #VotingWhileBlack podcast season finale to discuss my plans for criminal justice reform, fixing the racial wealth gap, and investing in Black entrepreneurship. When our community thrives, we all succeed. [link in bio to listen]
I’m running for president to show all children what is possible.

I knew getting in this race wasn’t going to be easy. Despite being up against billionaires and folks who’ve run for president before, I’m working day in and day out to meet folks one-on-one to earn their support. Link in bio to chip in today before our end-of-month deadline.

I stopped by Corinthian Gardens apartments in Des Moines more than a decade ago to canvass for Barack Obama. It was lovely seeing Glen again yesterday after all these years—and even more heartwarming that he remembered me.
